A pipeline of MATLAB functions to run Fieldtrip for EEG/MEG analysis

.bnd2lead.mni.warp: logical (optional. Instead of transforming the
       brain into MNI coordinates, you can wrap the grid onto it) (if .vol.type == 'template')
  ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.data: path of /data1/projects/PROJ/subjects/
  ERP_SUBJ, ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.derp: directory with ERP data
  ERP_SUBJ, ERP_GRAND, ERPSOURC_SUBJ
   
.endname: includes preprocessing steps (e.g. '_seldata_gclean_redef')
  ERP_SUBJ, ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.erp: a structure with cfg to pass to ft_timelockanalysis
  ERP_SUBJ

.erp.cond: cell with conditions (e.g. {'*cond1' '*cond2'})'
  ERP_SUBJ, ERP_GRAND

.erp.source: read virtual electrode data (logical)
  ERP_SUBJ

.erpsource.areas: how to speficy peaks to analyze, 'manual' or 'erp_peak' (peaks from granderp)
  ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.erpsource.bline: one number in s, the center of the covariance window
                     of the baseline (the window length depends on erp_peak) 
                     If empty, no baseline.
  ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.erpsource.cond: cell with conditions (e.g. {'*cond1' '*cond2'})
  ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.erpsource.erp: a structure with cfg to pass to ft_timelockanalysis
  ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.erpsource.erp_peak: struct with multiple elements (if .erpsource.areas == 'manual')
            .name: string ('name_of_the_time_window')
            .time: scalar (center of the time window in s)
            .wndw: scalar (length of the time window in s)
  ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.erpsource.keepfilter: logical, to keep filters or not (keep them only
                       if you plan to use erpstat or conn analyses)
  ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.erpsource.lcmv: options that will be passed to beamformer. Examples:
            .lambda: regularization parameter of beamformer ('25%')
            .powmethod: power method of beamformer ('trace' or 'lambda1')
            .refdip: location of the dipole for computing coherence to.
  ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.erpsource.refcomp: cell of string(s) of the comparison whose peaks
                    will be localized (one of the cells of cfg.gerp.comp) (if .erpsource.areas == 'manual')
  ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.gerp.bline: two scalars indicating the time window for baseline in s (only for plotting, TODO: check if necessary for normal analysis as well)
  ERP_GRAND

.gerp.chan(1).name: 'name_of_channels'
  ERP_GRAND

.gerp.chan(1).chan: cell with labels of channels of interest
  ERP_GRAND

.gerp.comp: comparisons to test (cell within cell, e.g. {{'cond1' 'cond2'} {'cond1'} {'cond2'}})
     but you cannot have more than 2 conditions (it's always a t-test).
  ERP_GRAND

.log: name of the file and directory to save log
  ERP_SUBJ, ERP_GRAND, ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.mod: modality, MOD in /data1/projects/PROJ/subjects/0001/MOD/NICK/
  ERP_SUBJ, ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.nick: NICK in /data1/projects/PROJ/subjects/0001/MOD/NICK/
  ERP_SUBJ, ERP_GRAND, ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.sens.layout: file with layout. It should be a mat containing 'layout'
              If empty, it does not plot topo.
  ERP_GRAND

.subjall: index of the number of subjects
  ERP_GRAND

.rec: REC in /data1/projects/PROJ/recordings/REC/
  ERP_SUBJ, ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.rslt: directory images are saved into
  ERP_GRAND

.vol.type: 'template' or subject-specific ('dipoli' or 'openmeeg')
  ERPSOURC_SUBJ

.vol.template: file with template containing vol, lead, sens (if .vol.type == 'template')
  ERPSOURC_SUBJ

 
